Every person deserves to be treated with decency

29
00:03:45,689 --> 00:03:55,773
and respect. Throughout much of history, mankind
did not see this. Dignity was seen as a virtue

30
00:03:56,529 --> 00:04:06,534
reserved to those of rank and privilege, kings
and elders. It took a revolution of the spirit,

31
00:04:07,029 --> 00:04:14,070
over many centuries, to open our eyes to the
dignity of every person. And around the world,

32
00:04:14,439 --> 00:04:21,590
generations have struggled to put this idea
into practice in laws and in institutions.

33
00:04:21,059 --> 00:04:31,118
So, too, here in Africa. This is the cradle
of humanity, and ancient African kingdoms

34
00:04:32,018 --> 00:04:41,100
