45
00:05:55,059 --> 00:06:03,124
With hundreds of millions of mobile phones,
surging access to the Internet, Africans are

46
00:06:04,024 --> 00:06:13,040
beginning to leapfrog old technologies into
new prosperity. Africa is on the move, a new

47
00:06:13,004 --> 00:06:16,066
Africa is emerging.

48
00:06:17,002 --> 00:06:22,060
Propelled by this progress, and in partnership
with the world, Africa has achieved historic

49
00:06:22,006 --> 00:06:30,015
gains in health. The rate of new HIV/AIDS
infections has plummeted. African mothers

50
00:06:30,069 --> 00:06:36,096
are more likely to survive childbirth and
have healthy babies. Deaths from malaria have

51
00:06:36,096 --> 00:06:43,169
been slashed, saving the lives of millions
of African children. Millions have been lifted

52
00:06:44,069 --> 00:06:51,161
from extreme poverty. Africa has led the world
in sending more children to school. In other

53
00:06:52,061 --> 00:06:57,083
words, more and more African men, women and
children are living with dignity and with

54
00:06:57,083 --> 00:07:00,083
hope. (Applause.)

55
00:07:00,083 --> 00:07:06,136
And Africa’s progress can also be seen in
the institutions that bring us together today.

56
00:07:07,036 --> 00:07:12,122
When I first came to Sub-Saharan Africa as
a President, I said that Africa doesn’t

